<1ST_LINE>u a AM-OfficersKilled     10-18 0312</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Officers Killed,0320</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two Policemen Killed In Separate Shootings</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By LARRY NEUMEISTER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An undercover policeman was shot and killed
during a drug buy and a patrolman was slain while responding to a
medical emergency in separate incidents Tuesday night, police said.
   The undercover officer was shot in the head and chest at 7:11
p.m. as he and another undercover officer tried to buy a gram of
cocaine at an apartment just west of Central Park in Manhattan,
police Commissioner Benjamin Ward said.
   In a gunfight that followed, a drug suspect was killed, Ward
told a news conference. A second suspect was arrested as he fled
the building and a third eluded police.
   The second officer was shot in the chest and stomach at 9:45
p.m. as he and his partner were getting out of their patrol car in
Harlem while responding to a medical emergency, said Officer
Virginia Conde, a police spokeswoman.
   Both of the officers died at hospitals, said Sgt. Raymond
O'Donnell, a police spokesman. The dead policemen's identities were
not released.
   In the first shooting, two men escorted the officers to the
apartment to buy drugs from a third man, and one of the three
accused the officers of being undercover police, Ward said.
   One of the three pulled out a .357-caliber handgun and shot the
officer. After the gunfight that ensued, the other officer ran into
the street and alerted backup police.
   The officer slain in the drug case was 26 years old and had been
a member of the force since 1984, Ward said.
   Mayor Edward I. Koch, who accompanied Ward at the news
conference, called the shooting ``an enormous tragedy. The partner
(is) terribly shaken. It's really overwhelming.''
   The officers had been attempting to carry out a buy-and-bust
raid, in which police purchase drugs from suspects, then arrest
them.
</TEXT>
