<2ND_LINE>PM-APME Citations,1676</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>APME Recognizes 288 Papers, Stations For Contributions</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-APME Awards</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press Managing Editors association
has awarded 288 citations to newspapers and broadcast stations for
outstanding contributions to the Associated Press report.
   The awards were presented Tuesday by Lewis A. Morrissey, metro
editor of The Flint (Mich.) Journal and a member of the APME
Citations Committee, at the annual APME convention.
   The APME is made up of managing editors and other news
executives of the 1,463 member newspapers of the AP, the world's
largest newsgathering organization.
   The AP is a cooperative agency whose members provide coverage of
news in their areas for distribution through AP bureaus in their
states.
   The citations are in three categories _ news, newsphoto and
news-newsphoto.
   Newspapers and broadcast stations cited in each category are:
</TEXT>
