<2ND_LINE>PM-Box Office,0448</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Filmgoers Put `The Accused' first at Box Office</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By LEE SIEGEL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``The Accused,'' an emotionally shattering tale
starring Jodie Foster as a gang rape victim, earned $4.3 million
last weekend to take the No. 1 spot in the weekly box office
listings.
   The film, which co-stars Kelly McGillis as a reluctant
prosecutor and is loosely based on a 1983 mass assault on a woman
at a bar in New Bedford, Mass., averaged $5,442 per screen in its
limited release to 796 theaters.
   ``Alien Nation,'' a police thriller that pairs cop James Caanaan
with a crime-fighting extraterrestrial, dropped to second place
with $4.25 million, followed by the Tom Hanks-Sally Field film
about standup comics, ``Punchline,'' which garnered $3.54 million.
   The fourth spot at $2.6 million went to ``Gorillas in the
Mist,'' starring Sigourney Weaver as zoologist Dian Fossey trying
to save the endangered primates.
   Director Joan Micklin Silver's ``Crossing Delancey,'' about
up-scale New Yorker Amy Irving's matchmaker-arranged romance with a
pickle merchant, placed fifth with nearly $1.2 million, followed by
the offbeat John Cleese-Kevin Kline-Jamie Lee Curtis comedy ``A
Fish Called Wanda,'' with $1.16 million.
   Bruce Willis' action bloodbath ``Die Hard'' was in seventh place
with $1.06 million, followed by Disney's ``Who Framed Roger
Rabbit'' with $1.04 million in eighth, and actor Tom Cruise's
``Cocktail'' in the ninth with $943,833.
   The comedy ``Big'' rounded out the top 10 with $903,280.
   Here are the top movies for the weekend as tallied by Exhibitor
Relations Co. Inc., with distributor, weekend gross, number of
theater screens, average per screen, total gross and number of
weeks in release.
   1. ``The Accused,'' Paramount, $4.32 million, 796 screens,
$5,442 per screen, $4.32 million, one week.
   2. ``Alien Nation,'' 20th Century Fox, $4.25 million, 1,436
screens, $2,961 per screen, $13.92 million, two weeks.
   3. ``Punchline,'' Columbia, $3.54 million, 906 screens, $3,910
per screen, $9.87 million, three weeks.
   4. ``Gorillas in the Mist,'' Universal, $2.63 million, 1,085
screens, $2,425 per screen, $12.66 million, four weeks.
   5. ``Crossing Delancey,'' Warner Bros., $1.17 million, 303
screens, $3,856 per screen, $8.81 million, seven weeks.
   6. ``A Fish Called Wanda,'' MGM@UA, $1.16 million, 937 screens,
$1,239 per screen, $54.81 million, 14 weeks.
   7. ``Die Hard,'' 20th Century Fox, $1.06 million, 968 screens,
$1,097 per screen, $74.14 million, 14 weeks.
   8. ``Who Framed Roger Rabbit,'' Disney, $1.04 million, 1,040
screens, $1,005 per screen, $143.27 million, 17 weeks.
   9. ``Cocktail,'' Disney, $943,833, 981 screens, $962 per screen,
$70.43 million, 12 weeks.
   10. ``Big,'' 20th Century Fox, $903,280, 834 screens, $1,083 per
screen, $106.68 million, 20 weeks.
