<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Soviet-Nuclear     10-18 0126</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Soviet-Nuclear,0129</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Soviets Conduct Underground Nuclear Test</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Soviet Union set off a nuclear bomb at an
underground test site to research the physics involved in a nuclear
explosion, the official Tass news agency said today.
   ``The radiation situation inside and outside the test area is
normal,'' Tass said.
   The test using a 20-kiloton bomb was a small one by current
standards that limit tests to 150 kilotons. It occurred this
morning at the Semipalatinsk Test Site in Kazazkstan in Soviet
Central Asia.
   Just five weeks ago, the Soviets conducted a test at that site
of more than 100 kilotons. That explosion was monitored by American
experts as part of an experiment to calibrate remote sensors for
verification of compliance with treaties.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
