<2ND_LINE>AM-Newspage Stocks,0106</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dow Industrials Climb To Highest Level Since Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices rallied in late trading Tuesday,
pushing the Dow Jones industrial average to its highest point since
the market crashed last Oct. 19.
   The market's best known barometer jumped 19.38 points to close
at 2,159.85, surpassing the previous post-crash high of 2,158.96
set on Oct. 10. But that was still 21 percent below the all-time
peak of 2,722.42 reached on Aug. 25, 1987.
   Tuesday's trading volume was moderate, and most of the action
centered around the issues of several big food companies that are
involved in takeover fights.
</TEXT>
