<1ST_LINE>r p AM-BRF--ColoradoPoll     10-18 0121</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Colorado Poll,120</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bush Leads in Weekend Poll for KMGH-TV</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Republican George Bush held an 11-point lead over
Democrat Michael Dukakis in a presidential preference poll
conducted last weekend for KMGH-TV, a station spokesman said
Tuesday.
   ``The Bush-Quayle ticket drew support from 44 percent, to 33
percent for Dukakis-Bentsen,'' said Allen Levy, an executive news
producer at the Denver station.
   He said the poll was conducted by Teichner of California by
telephone over the weekend. Pollsters contacted 600 registered
voters in Colorado. The survey has a margin of error of plus or
minus four points.
   In the presidential race, 18 percent said they were undecided
and 5 percent expressed support for candidates other than Bush or
Dukakis.
</TEXT>
