<HEAD>Nebraskans Back Bush, But Think Bentsen More Qualified Than Quayle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OMAHA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Republican George Bush has a 20-point lead
over Democrat Michael Dukakis in a poll of registered voters in
Nebraska surveyed last week.
   Of the 783 registered voters surveyed last week, 52 percent said
they supported Bush and 32 percent said they supported Dukakis.
   By a nearly 2-to-1 margin, however, Nebraskans believe Democrat
Lloyd Bentsen is more qualified than Republican Dan Quayle to be
president.
   The Omaha World-Herald reported on the poll in Wednesday's
editions.
   The poll conducted by SRI Research Center Inc. of Lincoln had a
margin of error of plus or minus four points.
</TEXT>
