<1ST_LINE>r a AM-CubanPrisoners     10-18 0296</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Cuban Prisoners,0306</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three Prisoners Released From Cuban Jail</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SANDRA WALEWSKI</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   MIAMI _ Three Cuban prisoners, jailed at least 20 years each for
their political beliefs, arrived in the United States on Tuesday
after they were released from a Havana prison.
   Dozens of family members waited expectantly at Miami
International Airport to welcome the prisoners, Angel Pardo
Mazorra, Alberto Padron and Valentin Figueroa Galvez, known as
``plantados'' for their resistance to political rehabilitation in
Cuban jails.
   ``Don't cry, we're together ... finally, finally,'' Pardo told
his mother as he embraced her.
   Moments before, family and friends formed a tight circle around
him, hands touching his hair, clothes and face as an emotional
Pardo walked across the U.S. Customs Service lobby toward his
parents.
   Pardo, 45, served 24 years of a 30-year sentence. He hadn't seen
his parents, Angel Padro Fuentes and Delores, in 18 years. Pardo
and Padron were sponsored by the International Rescue Committee.
   Figueroa, 51, who was jailed for 24 years and came with his wife
Maria, daughter, son-in-law and their 2-year-old daughter, was
sponsored by the U.S. Catholic Conference.
   Figueroa's brother Reinaldo, a former plantado, arrived in Miami
last month after being imprisoned 24 years in Cuba.
   Two other political prisoners who were expected to accompany
U.S. Rep. William Lehman stayed behind. One man refused to leave
for personal reasons, and the other had problems with documents.
   ``I'm very happy to have my freedom,'' an ecstatic Figueroa said.
   Earlier, Figueroa's mother Teresa nervously waited.
   ``I've always had faith this day would come and my family would
be together,'' she said.
   Lehman, D-Fla., said he planned to press for the release of four
more long-term prisoners that Cuban President Fidel Castro has
refused to allow to leave the island.
</TEXT>
