<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Phone     10-18 0299</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Phone,0310</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>MCI Earnings Up Nearly Six-Fold in 3rd-Qtr</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   MCI Communications Corp. said Tuesday its
earnings rose nearly six-fold in the third quarter on a 40.8
percent rise in revenue.
   MCI, the nation's second-largest long-distance company, said its
net income rose to a record $99 million, or 38 cents per share, in
the three months ended Sept. 30 compared with $17 million, or 6
cents per share, in 1987.
   Third-quarter revenue rose to a record $1.4 billion for the
quarter, compared with $994 million for the same period last year.
   The company said earnings were driven by strong revenue growth
from sales of 800-line and international services and gains in
commercial accounts as well as improved operating margins.
   ``Our success in increasing both volume and market share while
controlling costs has allowed us to take full advantage of the high
operating leverage that is fundamental to this industry,'' said
Bert C. Roberts Jr., MCI president and chief operating officer.
   MCI said the third quarter results included a pre-tax gain of
$11 million from previously negotiated antitrust settlements and a
pre-tax charge of $8 million associated with a contract settlement.
Results for the third quarter of 1987 included a pre-tax gain of $2
million from antitrust settlements.
   The results for this year's quarter also reflected a 7.35
percent dividend on $400 million of preferred stock that was issued
to International Business Machines Corp. in August. MCI also
completed the repurchase of about 47 million shares of common stock
from IBM.
   For the nine months ended Sept. 30, MCI earnings rose more than
fivefold to $219 million, or 78 cents per share, from $41 million,
or 14 cents per share, a year earlier.
   Nine-month revenue rose 27.6 percent to $3.7 billion from $2.9
billion a year earlier.
</TEXT>
