<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Earns-PPG     10-18 0176</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Earns-PPG,0185</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>PPG Posts 24 Percent Profit Gain in 3rd Qtr</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   PPG Industries Inc. said Tuesday its
third-quarter profit climbed 24 percent from a year ago as its
glass, chemicals and coating and resins businesses each showed
improvement.
   The company reported earnings of $112.9 million, or $1.03 per
share, in the three months ended Sept. 30 compared with $91.3
million, or 76 cents a share, a year earlier.
   Third-quarter revenue rose 8 percent to $1.36 billion from $1.26
billion a year earlier.
   For the first nine months, the company earned $365.3 million, or
$3.32 per share, up 30 percent from $280.6 million, or $2.34 per
share, a year earlier.
   Nine-month revenue rose 9 percent to $4.19 billion from $3.86
billion a year earlier.
   ``All of PPG's major business segments _ glass, coatings and
resins, and chemicals _ registered sales and operating earnings
growth for both the quarter and nine-month period,'' said Chairman
Vincent A. Sarni.
   He said the company expects to achieve record sales, earnings
and return on equity for the year.
</TEXT>
