<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0178</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Stocks Fall</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed slightly lower Tuesday in
active trading on the London stock exchange.
   Analysts said although the market has shown recent resilience,
chances for further advances appeared to be limited as the
Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index approached its
post-crash high of 1892.2.
   The FT-SE 100-share index fell 3.0 points, or 0.02 percent, to
1857.0, its lowest point of the day. The index rose as much as 3.8
points early in the afternoon, only to drop back in late trading.
   By the close of the day, the narrower Financial Times 30-share
index was off 1.4 points at 1509.5.
   The more broadly based Financial Times 500-share index was down
0.56 points at 1052.11.
   Overall volume was 561.8 million shares, compared with the 459.8
million traded Monday.
   Dealers said there was some disappointment over the lack of
leadership emerging from Wall Street, where the Dow Jones
Industrial Average was off 4.09 points at 2,136.38 by the close of
the London day.
</TEXT>
