<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market was mixed in moderate trading
this afternoon, after seesawing gently through much of the trading
session.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was down 4.09 points at
2,136.38 at 2 p.m. EDT.
   In the broader market, advancing issues almost evenly matched
declining ones, with 663 issues higher, 660 lower and 565 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board totaled 109.31 million shares.
   Analysts said most of the action continued to center around
issues of major food companies involved in new takeover bids.
   Market watchers also noted some underlying uneasiness in advance
of Wednesday's one-year anniversary of the October stock market
collapse.
   ``It's probably got some people a little uneasy,'' said Bill
Raftery, an analyst for Smith Barney, Harris Upham & Co.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
up 0.30 at 156.17.
   At the American Stock Exchange, the market value index had risen
0.19 to 303.46.
