<HEAD>Morgan Stanley Earnings Fall 28.1 Percent</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Morgan Stanley Group Inc. said Tuesday its profit fell 28.1
percent in the third quarter as revenue sank 15.7 percent.
   The parent company of Morgan Stanley & Co. said it earned $52.4
million, or $1.96 a share, for the July-September period, down from
$72.9 million, or $2.82 a share, a year earlier. Revenue, which is
gross revenue minus interest expense, fell to $423.8 million from
$502.9 million.
   For the first nine months of its fiscal year, profit rose to
$286.3 million, or $11.11 a share, from $199.6 million, or $7.83 a
share. Revenue rose to $1.61 billion from $1.43 billion.
   The company said a strong merger and acquisition business helped
make up for weakness in reduced revenue from underwriting and
commissions.
   It said its board had authorized the purchase of an additional
$100 million of its own stock.
