<1ST_LINE>u f BC-Earns-Drugs     10-18 0662</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Drugs,0681</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Third-Quarter Profits Up for Health Care Companies</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Strong gains in third-quarter earnings were reported Tuesday by
four leading pharmaceutical and health care companies, Merck & Co.,
Pfizer Inc., Eli Lilly & Co. and Warner Lambert Inc.
   American Home Products Co., a leading producer of consumer and
health care products, also reported a rise in after-tax profit, and
American Cyanamid Co., a pharmaceutical and chemicals concern, said
its operating profit rose strongly.
   Merck said its net profit rose 31 percent, Pfizer had a 17
percent gain, Lilly a 14 percent rise and Warner Lambert a 16
percent increase. American Home Products reported an 11 percent
gain and Cyanamid a 17 percent rise.
   Merck, based in Rahway, N.J., said net income for the quarter
totaled $311.8 million, or 79 cents a share, on sales of $1.47
billion. That compared to a profit of $237.6 million, or 58 cents a
share, on sales of $1.31 billion a year ago.
   For the nine months, Merck's earnings totaled $899.5 million, or
$2.28 a share, on sales of $4.41 billion. That was up 34 percent
from a profit of $674 million, or $1.65 a share, on sales of $3.67
billion in 1987.
   Pfizer, based in New York, had third-quarter net income of
$216.8 million, or $1.29 a share, on sales of $1.38 billion. That
compared to a profit of $185.8 million, or $1.10 a share, on sales
of $1.29 billion in 1987.
   For the nine months, Pfizer's profit totaled $649.7 million, or
$3.86 a share, on sales of $4.01 billion. That was 17 percent
higher than earnings of $553.6 million, or $3.26 a share, on sales
of $3.64 billion a year earlier.
   Lilly, based in Indianapolis, said quarterly income totaled
$171.4 million, or $1.20 a share, on sales of $940.6 million. A
year ago it earned $150.0 million, or $1.02 a share, on sales of
$845.8 million.
   For the nine months, Lilly earned $585.3 million, or $4.08 a
share, on sales of $3.02 billion. That was up 16 percent from
earnings of $505.5 million, or $3.44 a share, on sales of $2.73
billion in 1987.
   Warner Lambert, based in Morris Plains, N.J., said its
third-quarer profit totaled $87.6 million, or $1.29 a share, on
sales of $1.03 billion. That compared with earnings of $75.3
million, or $1.06 a share, on sales of $885.4 million a year
earlier.
   For the nine months, Warner Lambert's profit totaled $262.8
million, or $3.86 a share, on sales of $2.91 billion. That was up
14 percent from earnings of $229.6 million, or $3.20 a share, on
sales of $2.54 billion in 1987.
   For the nine months, it earned $262.8 million, or $3.86 a share,
on sales of $2.91 billion. That was up 15 percent from a profit of
$229.6 million, or $3.20 a share, on sales of $2.54 billion a year
earlier.
   American Home Products, which is based in New York, said its
after-tax profit in the quarter totaled $240.7 million, or $1.65 a
share, on sales of $1.41 billion. A year earlier, it earned $217.5
million, or $1.48 a share, on sales of $1.29 billion.
   For the first nine months, the company netted $693.54 million,
or $4.75 a share, on sales of $4.19 billion. That was up 10 percent
from earnings of $629.87 million, or $4.26 a share, on sales of
$3.81 billion in 1987.
   Cyanamid, based in Wayne, N.J., said third-quarter earnings
totaled $64.1 million, or 71 cents a share, on sales of $1.09
billion. That compared to last year's net profit of $66.3 million,
or 72 cents a share, on sales of $1.04 billion. Excluding a
one-time gain of $11.6 million from discontinued operations in the
1987 quarter, Cyanamid's earnings rose 17 percent.
   For the nine months, Cyanamid's earnings totaled $242.8 million,
or $2.70 a share, on sales of $3.14 billion. That was up 13 percent
from a profit of $215.4 million, or $2.35 a share, on sales of
$3.49 billion in 1987.
</TEXT>
